DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(81)90014-3
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199681900143
AB  - A non-linear tariff is one in which the total tariff paid by an individual is not proportional to the amount he imports. In this paper, we analyze optimal non-linear tariffs set by a welfare-maximizing government subject to a revenue constraint. The optimal schedule consists of a two-part tariff over an initial range of imports, and a continuous schedule for further imports that satisfies a modified Ramsey rule.
ER  - 
